Habitus (Fig. 2
A-B
) elongate, rather narrow, lustrous. Body colour mostly blackish brown to black; antennae and legs somewhat reddish brown; mouthparts reddish brown to yellowish brown.

Aedeagus (Fig. 5
A-C
) with median lobe thick, tubular; opening of apical orifice (Fig. 5D) large, subelliptical; left paramere (Fig. 6D) broad, subelliptical; right paramere (Fig. 6E) small, simply curved at outer margin, expanded in apical part. Endophallus as shown in Fig. 6F.

Female. Similar to male in general appearance, but distinguished by the following characteristics (Fig. 2
C-D
): mentum surface with fewer setae, less coarsely punctate; profemur without tooth on ventral side; meso- and metatibiae without calcars; abdominal sternum IV with lateral pits distinctly larger.
